-- Modules/Profiles/Core/GlobalCaptures.lua
-- The baked-in "global addon profile": ONE "!UUALL1!..." string bundling EVERY captured addon profile
-- (Details / Plater / … AND the UnbunkUtility profile itself). It is the code-side successor to the
-- per-addon BLOBS table in AddonProfiles.lua — a single hand-maintained string instead of many.
--
-- To refresh it: in-game, Refresh the addons you want (or "Refresh all"), then use the
-- "Global addon profile > Export" button at the top of the Import profiles tab, copy the "!UUALL1!..."
-- string and paste it below — KEEP the [=====[ ... ]=====] long-string wrapper (verbatim, no escaping).
-- On a clean install this ONE string seeds every capture (AP.GetBlob falls back to it), so a single blob
-- restores your whole setup. Empty = nothing baked (falls back to the per-addon BLOBS). If the blob ever
-- contained "]=====]", widen the wrapper by one '=' on each side.

local ADDON, ns = ...

ns.AP_GLOBAL_CAPTURES = [=====[!UUALL1!]=====]
